"title": "8122: friendship, with God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8122: friendship, with god",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A relationship of love and faithfulness into which God calls all people through faith.</p>\n<h2>Examples of friendship with God</h2>\n<h3>Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:23\">JAS 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:7\">2CH 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:8\">ISA 41:8</a></p>\n<h3>Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:11\">EXO 33:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:8\">NUM 12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:10\">DEU 34:10</a></p>\n<h3>Job</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:4-Job29:5\">JOB 29:4–29:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:20-Job16:21\">JOB 16:20–16:21</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of friendship with Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Mary, Martha and Lazarus</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:5\">JHN 11:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:3\">JHN 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:11\">JHN 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:35-John11:36\">JHN 11:35–11:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:1-John12:2\">JHN 12:1–12:2</a></p>\n<h3>The beloved disciple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:23\">JHN 13:23</a></strong> <em>“the disciple whom Jesus loved” is generally thought to be John.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:26\">JHN 19:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:2\">JHN 20:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:7\">JHN 21:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:20\">JHN 21:20</a></p>\n<h3>The disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:14-John15:15\">JHN 15:14–15:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The ministry of Jesus Christ is an expression of friendship to sinners</h2>\n<h3>In his life on earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:19\">MAT 11:19</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:34\">LUK 7:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:39\">LUK 7:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:7\">LUK 19:7</a></p>\n<h3>In his death on the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:13\">JHN 15:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:7-Rom5:8\">ROM 5:7–5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:4\">LUK 12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h2>God's delight in friendship with those who he loves</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:7\">ISA 5:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1-Hos11:4\">HOS 11:1–11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:3\">1JN 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>The reliability of God as a friend</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:10\">ISA 54:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:9\">DEU 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:5\">JOS 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:24\">PRO 18:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1\">JHN 13:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:5\">HEB 13:5</a></p>\n<h2>God's invitation for people to know his friendship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:18\">PSA 145:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:8\">JAS 4:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:20\">REV 3:20</a></strong> <em>Sharing a meal is a strong expression of friendship in Scripture.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:3\">ZEC 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:7\">MAL 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:27\">ACT 17:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4\">JAS 4:4</a></p>",
